To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Tennessee Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

Emails or texts sent to or from* any of the officials listed below with any of the keywords “Higher Education Reform Coalition,” “Council on Public University Reform,”  "Colin LeCroy," “Institute of American Civics”: 

Senator Becky Duncan Massey and/or her staffers;
Senator Bill Powers and/or his staffers;
Senator Bo Watson  and/or his staffers;
Senator Dawn White and/or her staffers;
Senator Ed Jackson and/or his staffers;
Senator Ferrell Haile and/or his staffers;
Senator Jack Johnson and/or his staffers;
Senator Joey Hensley and/or his staffers;
Senator John Stevens and/or his staffers;
Senator Ken Yager and/or his staffers;
Senator Kerry Roberts and/or his staffers;
Senator Mark Pody and/or his staffers;
Senator Page Walley and/or his staffers;
Senator Paul Rose and/or his staffers;
Senator Paul Bailey and/or his staffers;
Senator Randy McNally and/or his staffers;
Senator Richard Briggs and/or his staffers;
Senator Rusty Crowe and/or his staffers;
Senator Shane Reeves and/or his staffers;
Senator Steve Southerland and/or his staffers

* By "sent to," I also mean emails CC'd or BCC'd to the people named.

You may limit the search to the dates between December 1, 2021 and December 30, 2024.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 7 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Kent Hoover, a citizen of Tennessee, in coordination with Sophie Hayssen.
